OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FDry with a few bright spells at
OL,6,Ffirst but cloud will soon thicken and
OL,7,Flower with a band of rain following
OL,8,Fnortheast from mid-morning. The
OL,9,Fafternoon will become dry for a time.
OL,10,FWindy.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FDry early evening but
OL,13,Foutbreaks of rain soon push north
OL,14,Fbecoming heavy for a time around
OL,15,Fmidnight. Rain will clear to scattered
OL,16,Fshowers towards mooring. Windy.
OL,17,
OL,18,CMonday:FEarly showers soon clear east
OL,19,Fto leave the day dry with sunny
OL,20,Fspells. Heavy and blustery showers
OL,21,Fspread southeast from mid-afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
